American Electric Power - Wikipedia






















 






American Electric Power

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
  (Redirected from Appalachian Power)

					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


American Electric Power





Type

Public


Traded as



NYSE: AEP
DJUA Component
S&P 500 Component





Industry
Electric utilities


Predecessor
Originally American Gas and Electric Company (AG&E), formed in 1906 from Electric Company of America. Became American Electric Power in 1958; merged with Central and Southwest Corporation in 2000.


Founded
1906


Headquarters
Columbus, Ohio, U.S.



